hopobject.body: I never went to university onlymyhealth.com in marathi First, individual family members inherit positions in a trust that is run exclusively by a board of directors appointed by the family in a manner that is still not widely understood to outsiders. If you're a Sulzberger ski bunny or poet or schoolteacher angry that you haven't had a dividend payout since 2008, there's little you can do to pressure the family to sell up except appeal to these board members or try to get on the board yourself. But no board member who would be sympathetic would be likely to have been appointed to that board. So it's a nonstarter. (Again, Edmund Lee has more on this.)
